                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d243">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">703.94 Advisory Committee/24: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland (<persName type="from"
                            >Wilson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-03-17T18:00:00+01:00"
                            >March 17, 1933—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 17—2:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>151. Your 89, March 16, 8 p.m.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Under the terms of reference of the subcommittee it is not entirely clear
                        what its functions will be. The subcommittee may well devote itself largely
                        to fact finding.</item>
                    <pb facs="0343" n="241" xml:id="pg_241"/>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Even before receipt of your telegram it had been my intention to abstain
                        from unnecessary participation (as I quite recognize the possible
                        embarrassment) and to be guided by the instructions set forth in your
                            85.<note n="70" xml:id="d243fn70">Dated March 11, 7 p.m., <ref
                                target="#pg_233">p. 233</ref>.</note> However, since we cannot
                        foresee exactly the course of these discussions circumstances may arise at
                        which avowed incapacity on my part to participate might be more embarrassing
                        to you than discussion without commitment.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>I trust that I correctly interpret the sense of your instructions.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
